      "created_at": "2026-03-21T07:24:34Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-03-21T07:24:34Z",
      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "Thanks for the feedback and for sharing that PR, I wasn’t aware of it.\r\n\r\nThe goal here is a smaller immediate fix: for mixed-input transactions, the history RPCs should stop reporting sends and full fees when the wallet cannot attribute them objectively.\r\n\r\n#25991 seems to be an interesting direction, since with explicit per-output metadata the wallet can preserve the true send side. But that depends on additional wallet-local attribution being provided. Without that, we still need a safe fallback, and that is what this PR provides.",
